gomodel:SYNGO_524  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors performed immunogold EM in synaptosomal fractions from human cortex and detected huntingtin within the postsynaptic cytoplasm.\n\n13/6/2017 Pim\n- LIteral: \"Immunogold labeling of a synaptosome fraction from the human cortex demonstrates the presence of gold particles around vesicles (arrows) in a presynaptic profile and within the **matrix of the cytoplasm (small arrows) postsynaptically**.\". Experimental description: From M&M: Human brain tissue from three normal control cases was obtained from the Brain Tissue Resource Center at McLean Hospital, Belmont, MA.\n\nAntibody production:\nA peptide containing residues 1-t7 of huntingtin was synthesized to greater than 95% purity on a multiple peptide synthesizer (Symphony, Rainin). Amino acid analysis was performed by high pressure liquid chromatography to verify the sequence. A tyrosine residue was added to the C-terminusof residue 17;\nWhite New Zealand Rabbits (n = 3) were injected with a 1:1 ratio of Freund's complete adjuvant for the first injection and incomplete adjuvant for subsequent boosts at 4-6 week intervals." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-06-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_524" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

